            <creation>This story, with the short title "Bankrupt Youths Bring Mary Gifts," is recent: the earliest PEMM manuscript* in which this story appears is from around<date>1850</date>.Originally composed in <placeName ref="LOC3010Ethiop">Ethiopia</placeName></creation>
            <abstract>
                <p>Two pagan youths who hated Mary and insulted her constantly lost everything they owned. So, on the twenty-first day of Tarr (around January 15), they brought an offering to the church and confessed their sins against Mary. Mary forgave them, and they rejoiced to find their old lives restored.</p>
